{
  "analysis": "We are in a fresh terminal as root at /app. The task is to configure a git server that pushes data to a webserver on port 8080. Need to set up a git repository on the server (this machine) with a post-receive hook that copies the committed files to a web directory and perhaps runs a simple HTTP server. Since we have a clean environment, we must install necessary packages (git, maybe nginx or python3 for serving). We'll create a git repository at /git/server, set up a bare repo, add a post-receive hook that updates a web directory (e.g., /var/www/html) and start a web server on port 8080. We'll also need to ensure permissions and allow git push via SSH (but we can assume SSH already configured). We'll also create a sample hello.html after cloning and pushing from local, but we can simulate that by directly committing to the repo and testing curl. Let's start by checking the system and installing packages.",
